page.title: 10FAUNA
page.content: The wildlife in this area is quite plentiful with ample feeding places. there are no large woodland areas so large mammals do not exist. Rabbits, Shrews, Voles, Mice and Badgers frequent this region. There are many different types of birds. especially sea birds like the herring gull, lesser black-backed gull, oyster catchers, terns, curlews and a variety of ducks and geese. Sand martins are common in the area, as are the house martins, swallows and swifts. Many garden birds can be identified and include sparrows, warblers, tits, thrushes, blackbirds, finches and doves.
